<html><head><title>Aug 24th In-Testing</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Aug 24th In-Testing</h3><p>The test server has a new update today which includes player-title features.<blockquote><br>August, 24th Update 10:00am<br><br>Most changes lately have been related to the upcoming expansion and so aren't visible on Test. Here are a few things to look out for though.<br><br>- Changed the way no dispell spells work server side. You should not see a change.<br><br>- Changed the way MGB spells work server side. You should not see a change.<br><br>- Made server side changes to /targetgroupbuff. You should not see a change.<br><br>- Items with multiple "All Type" augments in them should not have all the augments pop out if you remove the top most augment.<br><br>- Wake the Dead pets should once again cast spells on Test.<br><br>- LDoN: Item Collect adventures should once again work on Test.<br><br>- Fixed a graphical issue with the guild management window when you resized it.<br><br>Custom PC Titles. The details are:<br><br>- The window can be brought up using the "<Shift>+T" key combination, this combo can be remapped via the options menu.<br><br>- The window should present a list of all titles available to the player and they can select any title listed.<br><br>- Selecting a title in the list should change the title shown above the player's head and appear in yellow.<br><br>- Clicking the "Change Title" button will change the player's title, turning it blue and updating all the players in the zone so they see the new title.<br><br>- Choosing "Clear Title" should remove any title from the player.<br><br>- GM granted titles should appear in the list and are selectable<br><br>- All players should retain their current title when they login, so it should not disappear because we have moved to a new system.<br></blockquote><br>If you want to check it out login to the Test Server.</div>